Seventy guests are being evacuated. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Emergency services have begun evacuating about 70 guests at the Centurion Hotel. The hotel's ground floor and surrounding areas are currently under floodwater. READ: Centurion Hotel flooded after heavy rains The property is currently inaccessible. According to the hotel, no one has been injured or is currently in danger. Torrential rains continue to wreak havoc in some parts of the country. Motorists have been warned to avoid roads that are flooded. Ten people, including three children, have been rescued during the Gauteng floods. The SA Weather Service has issued flood warnings for many parts of the country including Gauteng. Courtesy #DStv403